snippet.textDisplay:
It may be that you live on a cold rouge planet floating through the darkness of cold interstellar space, or a massve city contained within stranded space ship and the collective leadership of your society decide that everyone needs to be quarentined to the hospitals to be upgraded via horrific, gorry surgical procedures that involve mutilating the bodies of the subject first into a zombie-like monstrosity screaming in pain, and eventually dicing and slicing up the whole body into a souless, emotionless maniken-like cybernetic humanoid dubbed "cybermen". Your neighbors start dissapearing one by one, more of these cybermen start appearing one by one, and eventually it is your turn. It may be that you live in a wealthy, modern, instrustial society with a dark underbelly of wealthy inequality and corruption. Everything is controlled by one huge secretive corporation, and the initiate population control and create as much order as possible, they decide to turn as many people into their minions as they can via their dirty methods. Massive industrial factories start popping up everywhere, each stocked with countless booths with automated surgical machines to quickly slice open the heads of people, and put their brains into cold metal exoskeletons, on an indsustrial scale. People refuse, but using the dirty method of brainwashing like cattle, they are sent to the slaughter, where their humanity will die. It may be that you, your family, friends, neighbors, and everyone you know live on a peaceful alien planet on some corner of your galaxy. You have not engaged with any interstellar wars or conflicts and your planet has no raw materials that could attract an invasion. However the a war between the future, technologically-advanced, space-faring human empire and the Cyberiad rages in a sector, near your planet. This particular sector legion of Cyberiad have been reduced small numbers, are losing, and their damaged ship enters your solar system and they beam down to your planet. They are in desperate need of quick reinforcements and the bodies and physiology of your species happen to be very similar to those of mondasians and humans, and small but powerful force of cybermen decide to that everyone on your planet is sutible and prime for conversion. While you and everyone else outnumber these cybermen, all of you combined are still no matched for their advanced technology. They sieze everyone, including you, and you are all taken to their damaged space ship in orbit, where they will either lock you alive in the exosuits where you will be converted alive, or you will slowly be grafted with parts.


All of these are very different scenarios in very different parts of the universe, but they all end the same. You will be converted and upgraded.
